description: Delivered payments north of Â£7.6 billion to 30 million UK citizens in need, during Covid, and the Cost of Living Crisis. Operated as a full-stack developer on a multi-disciplinary nine-person scrum team for a large-scale critical UK public sector project by developing back-end solutions and spearheading architecture planning. Lead production runs and deployments.

Created a MVP prototype for white label charity app to be pitched to potential clients as a one-stop shop customizable CRM platform for their charity organizations. Used AWS cognito to set up authentication and presented components for UI to leadership.

Covered a wide array of Full Stack concepts and technologies, including cloud engineering with Amazon Web Services. Culminated in a capstone 3-tier application project, presenting to Accenture Leadership.

First point of contact in question, crisis or complaint for anyone related to the University. Liaised with managers and administrative staff on issues ranging from accommodation and well-being to finance.

Completed a Bachelor of Engineering in Electronics with a heavy focus on Computer architecture, Signal processing and Algorithmic thinking, at Warwick University. Achieved a 2:1 overall, with a 1st in my Dissertation, covering signal processing and design for Photoplethysmograph sensor with HR and SpO2 for Covid-19 patients.
